[[[break]]]added at line 16: *lime {code 
I think people enjoy using big words - perhaps when reading popular science, the public enjoy reading big words they think they understand, because it makes them feel smart. So journalists use them. (if you feel good while reading a magazine, perhaps you'll buy it again) And people don't really understand exactly what a paradigm is, but almost all have heard it (probably in business jargon) and have a vague idea of what it is, so it is an excellent big word to use in popular science type things. Before this course I had only seen it in Dilbert cartoons....u4309050
